fields.bio:
Leila Banijamali has founded businesses in the technology and fine arts industries and acts as business and outside general legal counsel to startups, entrepreneurs, and creative professionals. She is the founder of Bedrock, co-founder of Hive, which is an ideation and collaboration platform for entrepreneurs and idea-makers, and the lead singer and co-producer of the San Francisco band, Curse The Controls.

Leila's areas of practice cover strategic business development and transactional work for startups, including the drafting and negotiation of web and service agreements, intellectual property licensing, trademark application and prosecution, brand strategy, and online advertising (sweepstakes and contests). She was born in Iran and raised and educated in North Africa and Canada, where she enjoyed a brief professional tennis career, before settling in San Francisco. She continues to travel for both business and pleasure to almost every major city in the world and is fluent in English and Farsi.

fields.bio:
Roger Glovsky is a business/corporate lawyer and founder of Indigo Venture Law Offices, an innovative law firm committed to providing “high value legal solutions” for small businesses on a fixed fee basis.  With more than 25 years experience, Roger has a passion for helping entrepreneurs and business owners by turning complex legal matters into practical solutions. He is passionate about changing the way law is practiced in the USA--he believes strongly that every business owner, regardless of the size of his company should enjoy full legal protection and that legal documents protecting business owners should be affordable, accessible and comprehensible. Roger has over 25 years of experience as an attorney. He is co-founder of Indigo Venture Law Offices , and founder of LEXpertise.com. 

Roger started out as an entrepreneur working “in the trenches” as President of a software development company and then part of the management team of two venture-backed startups providing Internet related products and services, each of which raised over $20 million of capital.  In 2002, he started a solo practice, which later became Indigo Venture Law Offices.

Indigo Venture Law Offices provides legal counsel to traditional and web-based businesses throughout the business lifecycle - start-up, growth, and succession - with services that include incorporation, LLC formation, financing, mergers, acquisitions, employment, compensation (including equity incentive compensation), sales and distribution agreements, software and technology licensing, ecommerce, and Internet-related issues. 

With offices in Cambridge, MA and Louisville, CO, the firm offers a unique “solutions approach” to the practice of law. Our Venture Attorneys start by getting to know each client and understanding their business before applying our legal skills. The firm has pioneered the concepts for a new client-oriented business model by offering Legal Strategy Sessions, Three Levels of Service and Unmetered Consultations. For more information about Indigo Venture Law Offices, visit our web site at www.ivlo.com.

Roger is admitted to practice law in Colorado and Massachusetts.  For a full bio, go to http://www.indigoventure.com/attorneys/rglovsky.html.
